        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 5:08PM EDT by NWS Burlington VT</headline>
        <description>At 508 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Saranac Lake, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Saranac Lake, Adirondack Regional Airport, Lake Placid, Franklin,
North Elba, Wilmington, St Armand, Harrietstown, Jay, Brighton,
Keene, Black Brook, Santa Clara, Upper Jay, Ray Brook, Lake Colby,
Gabriels, Lake Clear, Onchiota, and Vermontville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
